The paper discusses local-search satisfiability solvers for propositional logic extended with cardinality atoms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The paper also describes techniques to reduce the problem to standard propositional satisfiability, which involves data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). Finally, the paper focuses on propositional logic (cs.PL) and its extensions, which is the main topic of the paper.
